From: conda-forge <conda-forge@example.com>
Date: Sun, 06 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Use dynamic OpenSSL and ZLIB in tests

conda-forge's openssl package ships shared libraries only; the static
variant (libcrypto.a) is not available. Remove the OPENSSL_USE_STATIC_LIBS
and ZLIB_USE_STATIC_LIBS settings so CMake finds the dynamic libraries
instead.
---
 tests/common/CMakeLists.txt | 4 ----
 1 file changed, 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tests/common/CMakeLists.txt b/tests/common/CMakeLists.txt
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/tests/common/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/tests/common/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -17,12 +17,8 @@ # nvcv_test_common ================================
 # Utilities used in unit and system tests. They don't
 # call the public API functions.

-set(OPENSSL_USE_STATIC_LIBS TRUE)
 find_package(OpenSSL COMPONENTS Crypto REQUIRED)

-# on some distros (e.g CentOS 7) we need to add libz when
-# linking against static libcrypto
-set(ZLIB_USE_STATIC_LIBS TRUE)
 find_package(ZLIB REQUIRED)

 add_library(nvcv_test_common STATIC
